/// Test workflow that starts a child and performs a long task (BT-1508).
///
/// Used to test that cancelling the parent propagates cancellation to the
/// child workflow per the parent-close policy.
///
///   engine startWorkflow: CancellableParentWorkflow id: "p-1" args: #(5)
Workflow subclass: CancellableParentWorkflow

  /// Start a child workflow and then do a long task.
  ///
  /// The child is started with default (#terminate) policy. After starting
  /// the child, the parent enters a long activity — this provides the
  /// window for cancellation during testing.
  class run: value ctx: ctx =>
    handle := ctx
      startChildWorkflow: SlowWorkflow
      method: #run:
      with: #(10000)
    // Do a long activity that creates a safe point for cancellation
    ctx
      runActivity: CancellationActivities
      method: #longTask:
      with: #(value)
    result := handle result
    #{#value => value, #childResult => result}
